		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I use NESASM3. Everyone bags on it, but yet a lot of times I see people use ASM6. I tried to use ASM6, but to me, NESASM3 is much more flexible and less of a hassle to use. Asm6 is just difficult.
<br />
<br />
<br />And then there's that CA65 one, not sure about that, but can't be that bad since more people use that I think.
<br />
<br />
<br />And yeah, they's how you do it with an assembler, but you can do it 500x faster and even comment your code and rewrite it in a matter of minutes. Even back in the day nobody hand typed the code in I don't think. @_@

		

